3
[p 
	[b 
		"Mega Turrican
	]b
	" is a Turrican 3 port from Amiga with slightly modified octopus boss at second stage.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Movie features:
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		"Emulator used: Gens 11a 
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Takes damage to save time
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Dies to reload bombs
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Plays on hardest difficulty
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	"Unlike the previous Turrican game, Universal Soldier, in this game you have a limited rolling power.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[b 
		"00FFBF23
	]b
	" - The most important memory address in the game (thanks for Sonikkustar!).
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"It depletes every 18 frame and when you enter the rolling mode. The rolling energy meter can also be seen below energy bar.
	$LF
]p
[dl 
	[dt 
		[b 
			"WEAPONS AND POWER UPS
		]b
	]dt
	[dd 
		[b 
			$LF
		]b
	]dd
]dl
[p 
	"-You can fire a shot every 7 frames, or every 8 if you want to use missiles.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"-Bombs do 30 damage, grant you an immunity for 55 frames or so and reloads for one piece at the end of a stage or part of stage.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"-Mines can be layed every 9 frames when you're in rolling mode. They do a whopping 6 damage per frame. If you exit rolling mode just after laying a mine, you have to roll until the wait time expires.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Red: 
	[b 
		"Multishot
	]b
	" - first one gives you three bullets and second one gives six bullets. You have to be relatively close to enemies to get all of them to hit. Best weapon in most places.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Green: 
	[b 
		"Laser
	]b
	" - does three damage to enemies, but some bosses' hit points are drastically lowered when you enter the fight with this weapon, so it's used a few times (Thanks for Sonikkustar for noticing!)
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Blue: 
	[b 
		"Rebound
	]b
	" - not worth mentioning
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Missile: 
	[b 
		"Homing missile
	]b
	" - if it has been 8 or more frames since you fired a shot last time, these little goodies come out of your gun. Normally they lock on closest enemy and do one point of damage. This increses bosses' energy by 8 hit points but still pays off pretty quickly
	$LF
]p
[p 
	""Green six": 
	[b 
		"Shield
	]b
	" - protects from damage for 10 seconds
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[b 
		"Heart
	]b
	": - Replenishes your energy until it's maxed
	$LF
]p
